  <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Lessons are typically 25 or 50 minutes long. You only pay for what you book, with no monthly commitment required. The platform uses a credit system, where you purchase credits in bundles and spend them when booking lessons. Some users find this system slightly less intuitive than straightforward per-lesson payment, but it does offer flexibility.</p>

  <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Compared to competitors, See Guru sits at the more affordable end of the market. iTalki's community tutors typically charge $4 to $15 per lesson, while Preply's tutors often start at $10 and go up to $50 or more. If budget is your primary concern, See Guru offers genuine value.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-white">Teacher Quality</h2>
  <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">See Guru has a large pool of tutors, which means quality varies considerably. Most tutors on the platform are from Southeast Asia, particularly the Philippines, where English is an official language and is widely used in education and business.</p>

  <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-neutral-300">What to expect:</strong></p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-neutral-400 mb-6">
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Strong conversational English:</strong> The majority of See Guru tutors speak clear, natural English. Many have years of experience teaching learners from around the world.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Varied qualifications:</strong> Some tutors hold TEFL, TESOL, or CELTA certificates. Others are professional teachers or have extensive informal teaching experience. Not all tutor profiles include verified credentials, so look for detailed bios and student reviews.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Inconsistent accents:</strong> Because most tutors come from Southeast Asia, you will primarily encounter Asian English accents. This can be helpful if you plan to work or travel in the region. Learners who want exposure to a variety of native-speaker accents may prefer iTalki.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Good availability:</strong> Time zone coverage is excellent for tutors from Southeast Asia, which makes scheduling easy for learners in Asia, Europe, and the Americas.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Our editorial team tested multiple tutors across different price ranges. Community tutors in the $5 to $10 range generally provided solid conversational practice. At higher price points, tutors were more likely to follow a structured curriculum and provide detailed feedback on speaking and writing errors.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-white">Platform Features</h2>
  <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">See Guru offers a functional set of features that cover the essentials of online language learning:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-neutral-400 mb-6">
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Credit system:</strong> Purchase credits in bundles to book lessons. One credit typically equals one lesson minute, depending on the bundle size.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Built-in video platform:</strong> Lessons happen directly on See Guru's website or app. No third-party software is needed.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Trial lessons:</strong> Most tutors offer a discounted first lesson so you can evaluate their teaching style before committing.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Tutor profiles and reviews:</strong> Each tutor has a detailed profile with their background, specialties, student reviews, and availability calendar.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Lesson recordings:</strong> Some tutors offer to record lessons so you can review them later. This feature varies by tutor.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Mobile app:</strong> See Guru has apps for iOS and Android, making it easy to attend lessons on the go.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Curriculum options:</strong> Many tutors offer structured lesson plans for specific goals, such as exam preparation or business English.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-neutral-300">Scheduling flexibility:</strong> Tutors display their available time slots, and you can book lessons up to several weeks in advance.</li>
