  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-white">Verdict</h2>
  <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">See Guru is a solid choice for budget-conscious learners who want regular 1-on-1 practice without committing to a subscription. Its pricing is genuinely competitive, and the flexibility of pay-per-lesson means you can learn at your own pace without financial pressure.</p>
  <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">The main trade-off is that you will likely be learning with non-native English speakers from Southeast Asia. This is not necessarily a bad thing, especially for conversational practice and pronunciation work, but learners specifically seeking native-speaker exposure may prefer iTalki or Preply instead.</p>
  <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Quality varies across the platform, so investing time in reading tutor reviews and trying a few trial lessons is worthwhile. Once you find a tutor that suits your learning style, See Guru can be an affordable and effective long-term tool for improving your English.</p>
  <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-neutral-300">Choose See Guru if:</strong> Budget is your top priority, you prefer flexible scheduling, and you are comfortable with non-native English tutors. Choose iTalki or Preply if you specifically want native-speaker tutors, formal lesson plans, or structured curriculum.</p>

